div.p:
It is not easy to understand why a gentleman should wish
            to possess objects of high cost that can give him no pleasure;
            and yet we see that purchasers of paintings will pay enormous prices for works which they have no capacity to enjoy;
            an instance of this kind is related by the reviewer which
            shows a most remarkable combination of simplicity and ambition on the part of the purchaser, and of a brilliant imagination and utter want of honesty on the part of the seller.

He has also nearly ready for the press, Bibliotheca Americana vetus: a
               Catalogue of Books relating to America from the Discovery to the year 1700;
               with notes and observations: in one volume, 8vo., of about 400 pages.
